[normal]About Arqiva[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva is a media infrastructure and technology company operating at the heart of the broadcast and mobile communications industry and at the forefront of network solutions and services in an increasingly digital world.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] Arqiva provides much of the infrastructure behind television, radio and wireless communications in the UK and has a growing presence in Ireland, mainland Europe and the USA.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva was responsible for UK Digital ‘Switch-Over’ – engineering from analogue television to Freeview – a huge logistical exercise which touched every Parliamentary constituency, requiring an investment by Arqiva of some £630m and was successfully delivered to time and budget.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva is also a founder member and shareholder of Freeview (Arqiva broadcasts all six Freeview multiplexes and is the licensed operator of two of them) and was a key launch technology partner for Freesat. Arqiva is also the licensed operator of the Digital One national commercial DAB digital radio multiplex.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva operates
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]five international satellite teleports, over 70 other staffed locations, and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]thousands of shared radio sites throughout the UK and Ireland including masts, towers and rooftops from under 30 to over 300 metres tall.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In addition for broadcasters, media companies and corporate enterprises Arqiva provides end-to-end capability ranging from –
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva’s WiFi network includes almost every UK airport – and reaches cross the hospitality and leisure sector, providing WiFi to 85,000 rooms in leading hotel chains, and many restaurants, retail chains and shopping centres and local high streets.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Elsewhere in the communications sector, the company supports cellular, wireless broadband, video, voice and data solutions for the mobile phone, public safety, public sector, public space and transport markets.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva’s major customers include the BBC, ITV, Channel 4, Five, BSkyB, Classic FM, the four UK mobile operators, Metropolitan Police and the RNLI.
